parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tailgate cables can cause the tailgate to collapse, potentially striking the bumpers or causing injury to individuals sitting on the tailgate, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The tailgate cables fracture or break
the tailgate collapses or drops suddenly
the tailgate strikes the rear bumper
the cables are bulging or showing signs of wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, catch fire, or experience various electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
headlights go out while driving
the horn sounds when the vehicle is parked and without keys
minor electrical problems
smoke and fire from the electrical system
and failure of various electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty wiring and electrical connections can cause electrical malfunctions, fires, and damage to the vehicle's electrical system, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Electrical malfunctions
smoke and fire from the electrical system
pinched or cut wires
and failure of various electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair and diagnosis of electrical system failures can lead to repeated failures, further damage to the vehicle, and increased risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Repeated electrical system failures
inadequate repair diagnosis
and failure of dealerships to identify and address the root cause of the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors and brake issues can cause the vehicle to vibrate, pull to one side, or sway while driving, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle vibrates at high speeds
vehicle pulls to one side while driving
vehicle sways left to right when the brake pedal is depressed
brake pedal feels spongy or soft
warped rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line failure can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle pulls to one side while driving
brake pedal feels spongy or soft
brake lines are leaking or damaged.
